Come on.

600
00:50:15,887 --> 00:50:17,806
You still have a lot.

601
00:50:22,310 --> 00:50:25,605
By the way, that looks like the jacket
I sold.

602
00:50:28,734 --> 00:50:30,318
Yours was probably fake.

603
00:50:30,402 --> 00:50:32,028
This is from the department store.

604
00:50:32,112 --> 00:50:34,948
This is a one-of-a-kind limited edition.

605
00:50:37,242 --> 00:50:38,910
Let me see!

606
00:50:39,578 --> 00:50:41,371
See? Look at this.

607
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:44,249
"HYH" Han Yu-hyeon! My initials are on it!

608
00:50:44,332 --> 00:50:45,834
Let me go. Let go.

609
00:50:45,917 --> 00:50:46,918
I said, let go.

610
00:50:49,546 --> 00:50:50,464
Hold on.

611
00:50:51,256 --> 00:50:52,966
Don't tell me you're…

612
00:50:55,010 --> 00:50:56,344
Are you "Debt No More"?

613
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:57,512
And you're…

614
00:50:57,596 --> 00:50:59,097
"Box Office Domination"?

615
00:51:04,978 --> 00:51:09,691
Actually, my real name is Ha Yeon-u… Hu.

616
00:51:09,775 --> 00:51:11,318
It's Ha Yeon-hu.

617
00:51:11,401 --> 00:51:14,029
As if. Everyone knows
that you're Yang Chun-sik.

618
00:51:14,112 --> 00:51:15,530
You're not fooling anyone!

619
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:19,743
-Let go.
-Is this mine too?

620
00:51:20,327 --> 00:51:21,411
Don't be absurd.

621
00:51:21,495 --> 00:51:23,705
-I'll just check my initials.
-Let go. It hurts.

622
00:51:23,789 --> 00:51:26,500
-It hurts.
-Don't pinch me!

623
00:51:26,583 --> 00:51:28,502
You're going to break my arm. My arm.

624
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:30,670
Don't scratch it. It hurts.

625
00:51:32,672 --> 00:51:34,633
-Come here. Give me that.
-I'm right.

626
00:51:34,716 --> 00:51:36,551
-You're going to scratch it.
-"HYH".

627
00:51:36,635 --> 00:51:38,094
It is mine, you idiot!

628
00:51:38,178 --> 00:51:41,223
You're probably the most curious

629
00:51:41,306 --> 00:51:43,099
about Mom and Ha-yeong.

630
00:51:44,976 --> 00:51:47,646
Mom moved into Ha-yeong's house.

631
00:51:48,563 --> 00:51:50,607
Grandma is staying at a nursing hospital.

632
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:52,609
-We visit her on the weekends.
-Is it good?

633
00:51:52,692 --> 00:51:54,194
Eat up, Mother.

634
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:56,571
Who are you?

635
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:58,657
Why are you eating with us?

636
00:51:58,740 --> 00:52:02,202
Mother, she's Ha-ni.

637
00:52:13,797 --> 00:52:15,966
You look so pale.

638
00:52:16,591 --> 00:52:21,054
You should have a big appetite
if you're young.

639
00:52:23,515 --> 00:52:26,184
Try this. It's tasty.

640
00:52:27,102 --> 00:52:29,479
Thank you, Grandma.

641
00:52:31,439 --> 00:52:34,734
You look like my granddaughter
when you smile.

642
00:52:35,610 --> 00:52:37,237
How pretty.

643
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:40,282
Is your granddaughter pretty?

644
00:52:40,866 --> 00:52:45,370
You bet. She's the most beautiful girl
in the world.

645
00:52:45,453 --> 00:52:47,038
She's my little puppy.

646
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:50,083
Grandma. What about me?

647
00:52:52,335 --> 00:52:53,503
Ok-jeong.

648
00:52:53,587 --> 00:52:57,132
Why did you bring this ugly girl again?

649
00:52:57,215 --> 00:52:58,675
I'm sorry, Mother.

650
00:52:59,217 --> 00:53:01,052
-They say you and I look alike.
-Hey.

651
00:53:01,136 --> 00:53:02,971
Don't say that.

652
00:53:10,854 --> 00:53:13,690
My beautiful, little puppy.

653
00:53:15,817 --> 00:53:17,736
My dear puppy.

654
00:53:19,696 --> 00:53:21,072
I love you.

655
00:53:22,115 --> 00:53:24,784
I love you even more, Grandma.

656
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:36,922
Right, Yu-hyeon and I

657
00:53:37,005 --> 00:53:40,050
-are slowly getting to know each other.
-It's warm.

658
00:53:42,302 --> 00:53:43,929
He's a chairman now?

659
00:53:44,888 --> 00:53:49,351
Judging by how my dad gave
the position to Do-yun so quickly,

660
00:53:49,434 --> 00:53:52,354
maybe it was his plan all along.

661
00:54:00,737 --> 00:54:02,489
Left foot forward.

662
00:54:02,572 --> 00:54:04,199
Right foot back.

663
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:05,867
Turn.

664
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:08,244
Let's change partners.

665
00:54:08,328 --> 00:54:11,790
All right, then. Let's do it again.

666
00:54:11,873 --> 00:54:14,793
One, two, three. Two, two…

667
00:54:14,876 --> 00:54:17,837
Now, you finally know how your father felt

668
00:54:17,921 --> 00:54:20,590
when you were busy having fun.

669
00:54:20,674 --> 00:54:23,009
I wasn't slacking off.

670
00:54:25,887 --> 00:54:27,472
I was busy getting these.

671
00:54:28,515 --> 00:54:30,058
It's amazing every single time.

672
00:54:30,850 --> 00:54:31,810
What is this?

673
00:54:31,893 --> 00:54:32,978
NAIL ARTISTRY CERTIFICATION

674
00:54:33,061 --> 00:54:35,271
You even got
a nail artistry certification.

675
00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:36,606
Please do mine.

676
00:54:42,153 --> 00:54:45,365
-What was that?
-I wanted to cherish your cute face.

677
00:54:46,116 --> 00:54:47,367
No.

678
00:54:48,702 --> 00:54:49,828
Let's take one together.

679
00:54:50,996 --> 00:54:52,247
All right.

680
00:54:53,415 --> 00:54:55,458
One, two, three.

681
00:55:02,966 --> 00:55:04,009
Okay.

682
00:55:10,932 --> 00:55:11,933
You erased them.

683
00:55:23,028 --> 00:55:24,612
Old lady.

684
00:55:25,822 --> 00:55:26,698
Close your eyes.

685
00:55:28,742 --> 00:55:31,661
-Why?
-Just do it.

686
00:55:39,419 --> 00:55:41,463
Okay. Open them.

687
00:55:47,218 --> 00:55:48,428
Is this a gift?

688
00:55:48,511 --> 00:55:49,679
What?

689
00:55:50,597 --> 00:55:51,931
Why do you look disappointed?

690
00:55:53,141 --> 00:55:55,477
Wait. What were you expecting?

691
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:58,229
I wasn't expecting anything.

692
00:55:58,313 --> 00:56:01,149
Gosh, this is so pretty.

693
00:56:01,816 --> 00:56:04,152
I made it myself.

694
00:56:04,235 --> 00:56:06,613
Do you know the meaning behind freesias?

695
00:56:07,322 --> 00:56:10,241
I only know the meaning behind lettuce.

696
00:56:11,743 --> 00:56:15,955
They mean "a new beginning."

697
00:56:19,084 --> 00:56:20,627
Thank you.

698
00:56:22,754 --> 00:56:24,172
I have something for you too.

699
00:56:24,255 --> 00:56:26,216
-What is it?
-Close your eyes.

700
00:56:26,800 --> 00:56:29,219
-What is it?
-Close your eyes first.

701
00:56:31,387 --> 00:56:34,933
I'm really going to be disappointed
if you give me snacks or something.

702
00:56:36,893 --> 00:56:38,228
Keep them shut.

703
00:56:38,311 --> 00:56:39,354
Okay.

704
00:56:58,456 --> 00:56:59,749
Shall we go over there?

705
00:57:00,250 --> 00:57:01,626
I saw something pretty.

706
00:57:05,755 --> 00:57:06,881
Wait up!

707
00:57:16,683 --> 00:57:18,977
Have you been waiting for a long time?
I'm sorry.

708
00:57:19,060 --> 00:57:21,896
I'm sorry to make
the great Min Gyeong-sik wait.

709
00:57:21,980 --> 00:57:22,939
I apologize.

710
00:57:24,774 --> 00:57:25,650
Jeong-man.

711
00:57:25,733 --> 00:57:28,403
Did you forget that I changed my name
ages ago?

712
00:57:29,112 --> 00:57:32,574
Oh, right. I've been so used to that name
that it just came out. Sorry.

713
00:57:34,409 --> 00:57:36,161
-Say it.
-What?

714
00:57:36,244 --> 00:57:38,496
Alexandro.

715
00:57:41,249 --> 00:57:43,334
-What?
-"Dro."

716
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:46,588
"Alexandro."

717
00:57:47,839 --> 00:57:51,134
You're good. Call me that, okay?

718
00:57:51,759 --> 00:57:52,927
Let's do that.

719
00:57:54,846 --> 00:57:57,307
What is this? Americano?

720
00:57:58,016 --> 00:58:00,185
Didn't I tell you I wanted a cafe latte?

721
00:58:00,268 --> 00:58:02,770
I was so used to buying coffee
for Anthony that I…

722
00:58:02,854 --> 00:58:04,856
I told you not to bring him up.

723
00:58:05,523 --> 00:58:06,524
-Get me a new one.
-Okay.

724
00:58:06,608 --> 00:58:08,359
It's so bitter.

725
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:09,569
I should gargle.

726
00:58:10,528 --> 00:58:11,863
Don't you forget.

727
00:58:11,946 --> 00:58:13,865
Two shots of espresso and a lot of milk.

728
00:58:13,948 --> 00:58:15,366
Unbelievable.

729
00:58:19,579 --> 00:58:22,165
He's worse than Anthony.

730
00:58:22,248 --> 00:58:25,084
Had Scarlett been here,
she would've taught him a lesson.

731
00:58:26,419 --> 00:58:29,506
Hello, everyone. I'm Kim Ji-hyeong
from Endless Challenges.

732
00:58:29,589 --> 00:58:32,383
I'm here with two very special guests.

733
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:35,970
They're in the Guinness World Records
for signing up for the most challenges.

734
00:58:36,054 --> 00:58:38,264
They're brothers Na Yeong-gu and Na Il-gu.

735
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:39,849
Hello.

736
00:58:39,933 --> 00:58:42,185
You two are truly incredible.

737
00:58:42,268 --> 00:58:46,439
May I ask you why
you've been challenging yourselves nonstop

738
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:47,982
for almost 40 years?

739
00:58:48,066 --> 00:58:51,277
For a very long time,
we had run a small store.

740
00:58:51,361 --> 00:58:55,156
We were average Joes
who had no particular talents.

741
00:58:55,240 --> 00:58:58,701
But challenging ourselves
to new things every day

742
00:58:58,785 --> 00:59:02,080
gave us strength and courage.

743
00:59:02,163 --> 00:59:05,333
It doesn't matter even if you collapse
or fail every day.

744
00:59:05,416 --> 00:59:07,961
When that happens, tell yourself this.

745
00:59:08,044 --> 00:59:09,671
"You're doing well.

746
00:59:09,754 --> 00:59:12,507
You're the most magnificent star
in your life.

747
00:59:12,590 --> 00:59:15,218
That is, if you refuse to give up

748
00:59:15,301 --> 00:59:17,053
and get back on your feet once again."

749
00:59:38,992 --> 00:59:41,369
That was the toughest and loneliest day

750
00:59:41,452 --> 00:59:42,954
in my entire life.

751
00:59:44,789 --> 00:59:48,876
I wanted someone to embrace me.

752
00:59:51,212 --> 00:59:53,965
That's when a miracle happened.

753
00:59:55,216 --> 00:59:57,927
Me from 20 years ago visited me.

754
00:59:59,679 --> 01:00:02,181
"Hello, me."

755
01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:06,519
And since that day…

756
01:00:09,522 --> 01:00:13,067
I gained the courage to start anew.

757
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:20,700
You'll probably never get this letter,

758
01:00:22,243 --> 01:00:24,704
but nevertheless,
I wanted to tell you this.

759
01:00:29,083 --> 01:00:32,045
I love you, Bahn Ha-ni.

760
01:00:33,296 --> 01:00:35,048
And…

761
01:00:36,382 --> 01:00:39,052
goodbye, me.

762
01:01:44,325 --> 01:01:46,494
Twenty years from now?

763
01:01:46,577 --> 01:01:47,829
LETTER TO MYSELF 20 YEARS LATER

764
01:01:47,912 --> 01:01:49,622
It's a frightening thought.

765
01:01:50,623 --> 01:01:53,292
How old would I look at the age of 37?

766
01:01:55,461 --> 01:01:57,422
I can't picture it,

767
01:01:57,505 --> 01:01:59,799
but I'd like to tell my future self this.

768
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,552
Dear future me,

769
01:02:03,553 --> 01:02:06,806
it's okay if you didn't turn out
the way I wanted,

770
01:02:07,932 --> 01:02:12,353
because I'm still the one who loves
and roots for you the most.

771
01:02:15,314 --> 01:02:16,399
So tell me.

772
01:02:17,442 --> 01:02:19,652
Can you confidently say
that you cherish me

773
01:02:20,528 --> 01:02:22,196
every single day?

